Sixteen people were injured on Sunday afternoon after a minibus taxi they were travelling in rolled into a swamp. The incident occurred at around 15:00 on the side of R730 at the Bronville crossing outside Welkom in the Free State, ER24 spokesperson Ross Campbell said. "ER24 paramedics arrived on the scene at 15:20 to find all the passengers had managed to get out," Campbell said. At least 14 adults and two children were treated on scene before being transported by paramedics to a nearby hospital. Campbell said the police and traffic department were also on the scene to investigate the incident.   GET THE NEWS at your fingertips and download the News24 app for Android or iPhone. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW New